vulnerable clients in attendance.

351
00:20:46,521 --> 00:20:49,022
- I think Roger knew him.
- Sorry to interrupt.

352
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:51,958
- It's Al Weaver from glo-coat.
- What does he want?

353
00:20:52,026 --> 00:20:54,361
- I don't know.
- Do you want me on the call?

354
00:20:54,429 --> 00:20:56,663
Didn't you talk
with him this morning?

355
00:20:58,066 --> 00:20:59,466
No.

356
00:21:15,883 --> 00:21:17,884
<i>- Al, how are you?
- Hello, don.</i>

357
00:21:17,952 --> 00:21:20,320
<i>I'm glad I could reach you.
I just wanted to let you know</i>

358
00:21:20,388 --> 00:21:22,956
<i>We appreciate everything
you've done for us,</i>

359
00:21:23,024 --> 00:21:26,059
<i>But we've decided to take the
account in a different direction.</i>

360
00:21:26,127 --> 00:21:28,528
<i>- All right, Al... - I want you to
know it wasn't an easy decision.</i>

361
00:21:28,596 --> 00:21:30,397
<i>- Now can I talk?
- Sure.</i>

362
00:21:30,465 --> 00:21:32,532
I don't think you understand
what's happened here.

363
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,401
And I'm not talking about
losing lucky strike.

364
00:21:34,469 --> 00:21:36,903
<i>- Lucky strike didn't enter into it.
- Really?</i>

365
00:21:36,971 --> 00:21:38,805
So that has nothing
to do with this?

366
00:21:38,873 --> 00:21:41,074
<i>Don, it's a simple coincidence
that it happened now.</i>

367
00:21:41,142 --> 00:21:43,944
Okay, you're right.
It is bad timing.

368
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,712
<i>How can you blame us
for wanting to move on?</i>

369
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:48,248
Because that commercial,
that little cowboy kid,

370
00:21:48,316 --> 00:21:50,650
Was the first successful
strategy you've been near

371
